Lewisham/Lewisham hospital
Homonym Number:
Word Class:noun
Sense Number:
Definition:
Origin:[none]
Register:
Register 2:
Domain:[none]
Region:[none]
See:
Pronunciation:
Notes: In Australia & NZ a hospital run by the Little Company of Mary, a Catholic order founded in Nottingham, England, by Mother Mary Potter. The name appears to be from the town where the first Australian hospital was established.
